  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q130-treated-in-concept-presumption-magnanimity-st-ii-ii-q130-a001-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q130.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">g contrary to the natural order, that any one should assume to do what is above his power: and this is what is meant by presumption, as its very name shows. Wherefore it is evident that presumption is a sin .</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d19">honor_worthiness</data>
</edge>
