  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q130-a002-treated-in-concept-presumption-magnanimity-st-ii-ii-q130-a002-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q130.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">e does exceed in proportion to his own ability, whereas the magnanimous man does not exceed his. It is in this way that presumption is opposed to magnanimity by excess.</data>
