  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">e fact that a man is praised, or shown any kind of reverence, he acquires charity in the knowledge of others. And since magnanimity is about honor , as stated above ( II-II:129:1 and II-II:129:2 ), it follows that it also is about glory : seeing that as a man uses honor moderately, so too d</data>
