  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Now for the doing of a great work, proportionate expenditure is necessary , for great works cannot be produced without great expenditure. Hence it belongs to magnificence to spend much in order that some great work may be accomplished in becoming manner. Wherefore the Philosopher says (Ethic. iv</data>
