  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Magnificence, in so far as it is a special virtue , cannot be reckoned a subjective part of fortitude , since it does not agree with this virtue in the point of matter : but it is reckoned a part thereof, as being annexed to it as secondary to principal virtue</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
